<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="367" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,764,1707,1973]" pageId="8" pageNumber="367">
This species was previously recorded from Ziéla, Guinean 
<collectingRegion box="[263,343,1742,1768]" country="Liberia" name="Nimba" pageId="8" pageNumber="367">Nimba</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="FAHR, J." box="[363,511,1742,1768]" pageId="8" pageNumber="367" pagination="450 - 451" refId="ref12727" refString="FAHR, J. 2013 d. Nycteris intermedia Intermediate slit-faced bat. Pp. 450 - 451, in The mammals of Africa. Volume IV: Hedgehogs, shrews and bats (M. HAPPOLD and D. C. D. HAPPOLD, eds.). Bloomsbury Publishing, London, 800 pp." type="book chapter" year="2013">
Fahr, 2013 
<emphasis box="[496,511,1742,1768]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="367">d</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
). A single specimen was also recorded during this survey on the Guinean side (
<bibRefCitation author="DENYS, C. &amp; B. KADJO &amp; A. D. MISSOUP &amp; A. MONADJEM" box="[222,469,1810,1836]" pageId="8" pageNumber="367" pagination="279 - 290" refId="ref12434" refString="DENYS, C., B. KADJO, A. D. MISSOUP, A. MONADJEM, and V. ANI- SKINE. 2013. New records of bats (Chiroptera) and karyotypes from Guinean Mount Nimba (West Africa). Italian Journal of Zoology, 80: 279 - 290." type="journal article" year="2013">
Denys 
<emphasis box="[315,375,1810,1836]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="367">et al</emphasis>
., 2013
</bibRefCitation>
). These two specimens (MNHN 1985-1143 and MNHN 2015-1357) were re-examined here. Greatest skull lengths were 
<quantity box="[151,256,1913,1939]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7399999999999998" pageId="8" pageNumber="367" unit="mm" value="17.4">17.4 mm</quantity>
and 
<quantity box="[312,419,1913,1939]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8199999999999998" pageId="8" pageNumber="367" unit="mm" value="18.2">18.2 mm</quantity>
, fitting the description of this species (
<bibRefCitation author="FAHR, J." box="[252,395,1947,1973]" pageId="8" pageNumber="367" pagination="450 - 451" refId="ref12727" refString="FAHR, J. 2013 d. Nycteris intermedia Intermediate slit-faced bat. Pp. 450 - 451, in The mammals of Africa. Volume IV: Hedgehogs, shrews and bats (M. HAPPOLD and D. C. D. HAPPOLD, eds.). Bloomsbury Publishing, London, 800 pp." type="book chapter" year="2013">
Fahr, 2013 
<emphasis box="[380,395,1947,1973]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="367">d</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
